textDisplay: No one could have ever imagined an anime with 12 endings for 12 episodes... It just sounds insane, all the effort that they must have done... Just straight up bananasEDIT: Thank you all for sharing other anime with a similar situation. I do feel that Chainsaw man still stands above them all because of the quality of the ending videos (they are really different from one another, take ending 3 for example), 12 different artists (and there are some big names among them). So those factors combined, makes it a really special case. But I stand corrected, it's not the first anime with a different ending for almost every episode.

textDisplay: Man Likely a Victim of Forced Organ harvestingYu Han told the story of her father.Yu Han, who currently lives in the United States, talked about what happened to her father. Mr. Han Junqing was a resident in Fangshan District, Beijing. He used to suffer heart disease and high blood pressure with both legs infested with pus all year long. Not long after starting to practice Falun Gong, his health improved dramatically. In addition, his bad habits such as smoking, alcoholism, and bad temper were gone.Mr. Han was arrested in March 2004 and held at the Fangshan Detention Center, where he was badly beaten by over ten officers. He died less than three months later and his body was cremated immediately.â€œI saw his body before he was cremated. He was terribly thin and bruised all over, but from his throat there was an incision all the way down to his torso,â€ his daughter recalled, â€œIn his stomach area, we could feel a hard block of ice beneath the skin that was stitched with thick black thread.â€The police said he died of heart attack, but Yu Han knew it was not true since her father had been healthy all along. â€œIt wasnâ€™t until three years later that I learned the truth â€“ tens of thousands of prisoners of conscience like my father had been killed for their organs. That night I cried for hours until I passed out...â€ she added. That is why she hoped the atrocity could be stopped so that other families would not have to suffer miserably like her.
textOriginal:
Man Likely a Victim of Forced Organ harvesting

Yu Han told the story of her father.

Yu Han, who currently lives in the United States, talked about what happened to her father. Mr. Han Junqing was a resident in Fangshan District, Beijing. He used to suffer heart disease and high blood pressure with both legs infested with pus all year long. Not long after starting to practice Falun Gong, his health improved dramatically. In addition, his bad habits such as smoking, alcoholism, and bad temper were gone.

Mr. Han was arrested in March 2004 and held at the Fangshan Detention Center, where he was badly beaten by over ten officers. He died less than three months later and his body was cremated immediately.

â€œI saw his body before he was cremated. He was terribly thin and bruised all over, but from his throat there was an incision all the way down to his torso,â€ his daughter recalled, â€œIn his stomach area, we could feel a hard block of ice beneath the skin that was stitched with thick black thread.â€

The police said he died of heart attack, but Yu Han knew it was not true since her father had been healthy all along. â€œIt wasnâ€™t until three years later that I learned the truth â€“ tens of thousands of prisoners of conscience like my father had been killed for their organs. That night I cried for hours until I passed out...â€ she added. That is why she hoped the atrocity could be stopped so that other families would not have to suffer miserably like her.
